Halfling

Appearance

They look like humans, but they have slightly larger ears and hairier feet. They are also much smaller, barely rising to the waist of average humans.

Naming Convention

They tend to be regarded as having silly names such as Bilbo or Drogo, with last names such as Trickfoot or Taloon.

Biology

They have fairly run of the mill physical characteristics save for the fact their tallest specimen on record is just under four feet tall. They are proportionally the same as humans just on a smaller scale. Their larger ears don't particularly increase their hearing capability, but their larger, sturdy feet do give them an advantage when circumstances call for being barefoot.

Geography

Halflings have a few small settlements in the kingdoms of Wyrion and within the Valley of Colors, but the majority have integrated with the society we know and expect from Erendia.
